<meta name="socialpost1" content="Cherise Doyley never expected to see a judge while in labor. Yet she found herself fighting a court for the right to make medical decisions about her own body — from her hospital bed. Here’s how her case unfolded." />
<meta name="socialpost2" content="Courts have found time and time again that you can’t force someone to undergo medical treatment. Pregnant patients are the rare exception. Watch how one woman found herself before a judge while she was still in labor." />
<meta name="socialpost3" content="“Now this is the craziest thing I’ve ever seen,” said Cherise Doyley when nurses wheeled a tablet up to her hospital bed and informed her she was in court. The reason? She had refused a C-section." />
